<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6587> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6587" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Pr. and then Procos. when he governed Hither Spain in the late second century (CIL 1(2).2.840; see 110, Promagistrates)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3450> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3450" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "These two names appear, that of Fabius with the title Procos., on milestones found near Lerida in Hither Spain (CIL 1\n     .2.823, 824, and on Sergius, 840; cf. ILS 5812, 5813). The date is uncertain, and obviously the two governors should be dated in different years. Wilsdorf (94f.) suggested a date about the middle of the second century, but Münzer (RE) favors one toward the end." .
